Cultural Practices Survey

Help us understand the rich cultural diversity of India by sharing your knowledge about regional practices and traditions.

Purpose of This Survey

This survey explores cultural practices - the everyday beliefs, behaviors, values, and traditions that are shared within your cultural region. Your responses will contribute to a comprehensive understanding of India's diverse cultural landscape and help preserve valuable cultural knowledge for future generations.

What to Expect

  • Questions about various aspects of cultural life in your region
  • Estimated completion time: 2-3 hours (you can save and continue later)
  • Your progress will be automatically saved as you go
  • You can navigate between sections and return to previous questions

Important Guidelines

  • All responses are anonymous and confidential
  • Answer based on your personal knowledge and experience of your region
  • There are no right or wrong answers - we value your authentic perspective
  • If you're unfamiliar with a practice, you can specify "none" or explain what you do know
  • Please provide thoughtful, detailed responses when possible
  • You can pause and resume the survey at any time

Your Contribution Matters

By participating in this survey, you are helping to:

  • Document and preserve India's rich cultural heritage
  • Support academic research in anthropology and cultural studies
  • Enhance cross-cultural understanding within India
  • Create a valuable resource for future generations

By continuing, you agree to participate in this research study.
